      "content": "i see what u mean about the prestige thing, but let's dig a bit deeper into the \"leadership\" aspect you mentioned. specifically for a role that involves managing senior stakeholders and lots of high-level meetings. \n\nwhen you look at the names and where they went to school, do you see any differences in how they might navigate our corporate culture here in the US vs just being good at the tech side? like, are there subtle indicators in their backgrounds that suggest who would be more \"natural\" in a leadership/client-facing role here?",
